identificationRemarks: Needs further study! This specimen is lower in altitude than typical. It has the bicolored leaf pubescence of E. coloradense, the stem pubescence (altho somewhat sparse) of E. pauciflorum or E. brandegeei and the erect habit of E. brandegeei. It does not appear to be densely matted. Based on geography it is not likely E. pauciflorum.
